    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-01-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/43.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 25.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The minister for foreign affairs told me this
                    morning that the Haitian Government had refused to accept Santo Domingo’s
                    proposition for a joint commission as outlined in my last cable. A commission
                    from Haiti is now at the frontier with the Haitian minister to Santo Domingo.
                    Santo Domingo has also sent two commissioners. These commissioners and the
                    Haitian commission are expected to arrive at some satisfactory <hi rend="italic"
                        >modus vivendi</hi>. The Dominican troops are still at the scene, but are
                    expected to be withdrawn very soon.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William W. Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
